; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/qk-matvec-split.fk form-stdlib/qk-matvec-lane.fk form-stdlib/qk-matmul-batch.fk
;
; qk-matmul-batch-band — the token tiling, the grid inversion, the per-token association identity, and
; the claim that batching needs NO new epsilon. Proven without a GPU.
;
; qk-matmul-batch.fk turns the matvec into a matmul by giving one SIMD group EIGHT accumulators and one
; weight decode. Four things can be wrong in ways no GPU run would reveal, because each still produces
; a plausible number:
;
;   - THE TOKEN TILING. `ntile = ceil(ntok/8)` with a guarded tail is an off-by-one waiting to happen at
;     every batch size that is not a multiple of 8 — and a prompt is almost never a multiple of 8. Drop
;     the last token of a batch and the prefill is short one position: the KV cache is missing a row,
;     attention still runs, a token still comes out, and it is wrong. So the tiling is checked AS a
;     partition of [0, ntok): the tile counts must sum to EXACTLY ntok, at multiples of 8, at one above
;     and one below, at 1, and at a real prompt length.
;   - THE GRID INVERSION. The kernel recovers (row, tile) from gid/32 by integer division. If the row
;     and the tile are ever swapped or the divisor drifts from ntile, every thread computes a real row
;     of a real tensor and writes it to the wrong place. Checked by inverting: for every group index,
;     row-of and tile-of must rebuild it.
;   - THE ASSOCIATION IDENTITY. The cell's central safety claim is that batching reassociates NOTHING —
;     that token t's sum inside the batched kernel is bit-for-bit the lane kernel's sum for token t, so
;     no epsilon at all is needed beyond the one qk-matvec-lane.fk already carries. That is an equation
;     and is checked as one, including on the catastrophic-cancellation fixture where the lane fold and
;     the plain right fold are KNOWN to disagree — if the batched sum silently became the plain fold,
;     bit 8 of qk-matvec-lane-band would still pass and this one would not.
;   - THE BOUND'S PROVENANCE. qmb-bound-coeff must BE qml-bound-coeff, which must BE qms-bound-coeff at
;     parts=32. Checked transitively at four widths, so "no new derivation" stays an identity rather
;     than becoming decoration.
;
; WHAT THIS BAND DOES NOT SPEAK FOR — its radius, and it is narrower than it looks.
;   * It speaks for the TILING, the GRID, the association IDENTITY and the emitted TEXT's shape, in
;     Form's fp64, on small fixtures.
;   * It does NOT speak for the batched kernel being bit-exact against P separate lane matvecs IN f32
;     ON THE GPU. That claim is about an emitted kernel's rounding and cannot be settled in Form: it is
;     form/native/metal/metal_batched_prefill.sh's GATE B2, which runs the batched kernel against P
;     sequential lane matvecs on real llama3.2:3b tensors at four batch sizes and demands zero differing
;     floats out of P*rows.
;   * It does NOT speak for metal::simd_sum's association, for the MSL compiling, for the GPU, or for a
;     token. It cannot execute any of them.
;   * It does NOT speak for the CARRIER's decision to dispatch the decode kernels once per token for
;     RMSNorm / RoPE / attention. That is bit-exact by construction (the same binary) and is gated
;     end-to-end by the same harness demanding unchanged token ids.
;   * It does NOT speak for any SIMD width other than 32, nor for any tile other than 8. Bits 1 and 128
;     pin both constants so a later edit cannot widen them silently while the emitted text still spells
;     the old literal.
;
; Kin: qk-matmul-batch.fk (under test), qk-matvec-lane.fk (qml-lane-sum / qml-bound-coeff — the
; association and the bound this must reproduce unchanged), qk-matvec-split.fk (qms-bound-coeff,
; qms-serial-sum), qk-matvec-lane-band.fk (the band shape this follows).
;
; Verdict 255 when the batched matmul is honest:
;   1   THE TILE IS NAMED            qmb-tile = 8, and both emitted kernels spell the same 8
;   2   IT IS A PARTITION            the tile counts sum to EXACTLY ntok at six batch sizes, including
;                                    non-multiples of 8, ntok = 1, and a real prompt length
;   4   THE GRID INVERTS             row-of and tile-of rebuild every group index of a real shape
;   8   THE ASSOCIATION IS UNCHANGED qmb-token-sum = qml-lane-sum on fixtures — and on the fixture
;                                    where the lane fold is KNOWN to differ from the plain right fold,
;                                    so the equality cannot be an artifact of a blind fixture
;   16  THE BOUND IS ALREADY DERIVED qmb-bound-coeff = qml-bound-coeff = qms-bound-coeff(cols, 32),
;                                    transitively, at four widths
;   32  NO TAIL IS LOST              the last tile of a non-multiple batch carries exactly the
;                                    remainder, and no tile is ever empty except past the end
;   64  TWO KERNELS, TWO QUANTS      each text declares its own kernel name; the appendix is EXACTLY
;                                    the two concatenated; and the Q6_K and Q4_K texts are the same
;                                    LENGTH and NOT the same TEXT (a copy-paste that forgot to swap
;                                    q6k for q4k, or 210 for 144, would make them equal)
;   128 EIGHT ACCUMULATORS, LITERAL  the declaration spells `float acc[8]` and the emitted step spells
;                                    the same 8 — the tile is a literal for a reason (registers, not
;                                    local memory), so the literal is pinned to the name

(do
    (defn qbb-mod (a n) (sub a (mul (div a n) n)))
    (defn qbb-opens-with (s p)
        (if (lt (str_len s) (str_len p)) 0
            (if (str_eq (substring s 0 (str_len p)) p) 1 0)))
    (defn qbb-has (s p)
        (if (lt (str_len s) (str_len p)) 0
            (if (str_eq (substring s 0 (str_len p)) p) 1 (qbb-has (substring s 1 (str_len s)) p))))

    ; --- 1: the tile is named, once ---
    (let c0 (if (eq (qmb-tile) 8) 1 0))

    ; --- 2: a real partition of the token range. Six batch sizes, chosen so the ceiling arithmetic is
    ; exercised where it breaks: a clean multiple, one above and one below a multiple, ntok = 1 (the
    ; degenerate batch that is also the decode path's shape), a real prompt length, and a chunk. ---
    (let c1 (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 8) 8)
            (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 9) 9)
            (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 7) 7)
            (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 1) 1)
            (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 6) 6)
            (if (eq (qmb-cover-count 64) 64) 2 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; --- 4: the grid inverts. Every group index must rebuild from row-of and tile-of, and the tile
    ; index must be inside ntile — a swapped pair or a drifted divisor writes real numbers to wrong
    ; rows, which no epsilon would ever catch. ---
    (defn qbb-inv (rows ntok g)
        (if (ge g (qmb-groups rows ntok)) 1
            (do
                (let r (qmb-row-of g ntok))
                (let p (qmb-tile-of g ntok))
                (if (lt p (qmb-ntile ntok))
                    (if (eq (add (mul r (qmb-ntile ntok)) p) g)
                        (if (lt r rows) (qbb-inv rows ntok (add g 1)) 0) 0) 0))))
    (let c2 (if (eq (qbb-inv 64 6 0) 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-inv 17 9 0) 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-inv 5 1 0) 1) 4 0) 0) 0))

    ; --- 8: the association is UNCHANGED, and the fixture proves it is not a blind one. The 34-element
    ; fixture is qk-matvec-lane-band's: index 0 = 1.0, 32 = 1e16, 33 = -1e16. The lane fold and the
    ; plain right fold DISAGREE on it. The batched sum must equal the LANE one and therefore must also
    ; differ from the plain one — if tiling had quietly collapsed the fold, both halves would fail. ---
    (defn qbb-mk (i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) (reverse acc)
            (qbb-mk (add i 1) n
                (cons (if (eq i 0) 1.0 (if (eq i 32) 1e16 (if (eq i 33) -1e16 0.0))) acc))))
    (let xs (qbb-mk 0 34 (list)))
    (defn qbb-ramp (i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) (reverse acc) (qbb-ramp (add i 1) n (cons (add (mul i 0.25) 0.5) acc))))
    (let ys (qbb-ramp 0 100 (list)))
    (let c3 (if (eq (qmb-token-sum xs 34) (qml-lane-sum xs 34))
            (if (eq (qmb-token-sum ys 100) (qml-lane-sum ys 100))
            (if (eq (qmb-token-sum xs 34) (qms-serial-sum xs 34)) 0 8) 0) 0))

    ; --- 16: the bound needs no new derivation, transitively, and that is an EQUATION ---
    (defn qbb-boundeq (cols)
        (if (eq (qmb-bound-coeff cols) (qml-bound-coeff cols))
            (if (eq (qmb-bound-coeff cols) (qms-bound-coeff cols 32)) 1 0) 0))
    (let c4 (if (eq (qbb-boundeq 3072) 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-boundeq 8192) 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-boundeq 1024) 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-boundeq 33) 1) 16 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; --- 32: no tail is lost and no tile is spuriously empty. The remainder tile must carry exactly
    ; the remainder; every earlier tile must be full; a tile past the end must be 0. ---
    (let c5 (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 0 6) 6)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 0 9) 8)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 1 9) 1)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 1 8) 0)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 7 64) 8)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile-n 8 64) 0) 32 0) 0) 0) 0) 0) 0))

    ; --- 64: two kernels, two quants, one meaning. Each declares its own name; the appendix is EXACTLY
    ; the two; and they are the same LENGTH but NOT the same TEXT — which is what a copy-paste that
    ; forgot to swap q6k/q4k or 210/144 would break. ---
    (let k6 (qmb-batch-msl "form_q6k_matmul_batch_f32" "q6k" "210"))
    (let k4 (qmb-batch-msl "form_q4k_matmul_batch_f32" "q4k" "144"))
    (let c6 (if (eq (qbb-opens-with k6 "kernel void form_q6k_matmul_batch_f32 ") 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-opens-with k4 "kernel void form_q4k_matmul_batch_f32 ") 1)
            (if (eq (str_len k6) (str_len k4))
            (if (str_eq k6 k4) 0
            (if (eq (str_len (qmb-msl-appendix)) (add (str_len k6) (str_len k4))) 64 0)) 0) 0) 0))

    ; --- 128: eight accumulators, spelled as a literal in BOTH the declaration and the step, and the
    ; literal is pinned to the name. A dynamically-indexed array would spill to local memory and lose
    ; the entire win, so the literal is deliberate and must stay in step with qmb-tile. ---
    (let c7 (if (eq (qbb-has (qmb-decl) "float acc[8];") 1)
            (if (eq (qbb-has (qmb-step "q6k" "210") "for (uint i = 0; i < 8u; ++i)") 1)
            (if (eq (qmb-tile) 8) 128 0) 0) 0))

    (add c0 (add c1 (add c2 (add c3 (add c4 (add c5 (add c6 c7))))))))
